@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Permutax" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 4 colours.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Permutax runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on two tiles, these tiles will swap their
positions. If one or more neighbouring tiles match these tiles, all
neighbouring tiles that are of the same type will be removed from
the board and you will get points according to the number of tiles
that match. as shown below:

  2 matching tiles =  1 point
  3 matching tiles =  4 points
  4 matching tiles =  8 points
  5 matching tiles = 16 points

  One important thing to remember: do not isolate one or more
tiles, because the number of isolated tiles accumulates as the
game is played, and when that number reaches 10, the game ends.

  When a game board is completed, Permutax displays if one or more
tiles have been left on the board, the score you made on that board
and the total score you have made up to now.

  If you have completed all 25 game boards, Permutax restarts at
the first game board and the game continues... until you have
isolated a tenth tile...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

